"Sharing system error log information with us helps us to improve our products. Because of certain design characteristics in the Andriod system, when you share this information with us, there is a small possibility that some personal information may be attached, such as your telephone number, email address or Facebook account number. We will not use it for personal identity recognition and we will not share your information with any third party for any purpose. Your decision as to whether or not you wish to share wrong system log information with us will have no implications for your future dealings with OnePlus. After choosing to share system error data with OnePlus, you can still stop the process at any time. "I. Preamble 1.1 Please be aware that OnePlus attaches importance to the privacy of users and tries to take effective measures to protect user privacy. 1.2 WHEREAS, when you use services provided by OnePlus, OnePlus may collect and use your relevant information. OnePlus hopes, through this Privacy Policy, to show you how OnePlus will collect, use, store and share these information, and the way of accessing, updating, controlling, and protecting these information, which OnePlus provides to you. 1.3 This Privacy Policy is closely related to the services of OnePlus which you use, and we hope you read it carefully. When necessary, please follow the guidelines in this Privacy Policy to make a choice which you think appropriate. 1.4 Your use or continuous use of OnePlus's services means that you agree OnePlus to collect, use, store and share your information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. II. InformationOnePlus May Collect When providing services to you, OnePlus may collect, store and use the following information related to you. If you do not provide relevant information, you may not be able to register as an OnePlus user or cannot enjoy some services provided by OnePlus, or cannot obtain the desired effects of relevant services. 2.1 Information Provided by You 2.2.1 Related personal information such as name, phone number, email, mailing address and bank account number, etc. provided by you to OnePlus when you register an OnePlus account or use OnePlus's services; 2.2.2 Shared information (such as sharing albums, diary mood, event reviews, etc.) provided by you to other parties through OnePlus's services, and information stored when you use OnePlus's services. 2.2 Your Information Shared by Other Parties Your shared information provided by other parties related to you when such other parties use OnePlus's services. 2.3 Your Information Obtained by OnePlus When you use OnePlus's services, OnePlus may collect your following information: 2.3.1 Log information: refers to technical information automatically collected by the system through cookies, web beacon or otherwise when you use OnePlus's services, including: (a) device or software information, such as device name and model, device identification number (IMEI), operating system version number, android version number, device selected language, SIM card telecom operator and country; (b) information searched or browsed by you when using OnePlus's services, such as your used web search terms and your visited social media page URL addresses, and other information and content details browsed by you or provided as required by you when you use OnePlus's services; (c) information which you use for communication through OnePlus's services, such as communication account number, and the time, data and duration of communication; (d) information (metadata) contained in contents which you share through OnePlus's services, such as the date, time, or location of shared photographs or videos shot or uploaded. 2.3.2 Location information: refers to the information on your location, which is collected when you open the device location function and use relevant services provided by OnePlus based on location, including: (a) your geographic location information collected by GPS or WiFi, etc. when you use OnePlus's services through mobile devices with positioning function; (b) real-time information including your geographic location provided by you or other users, such as your geographic information contained in account information provided by you, or shared information showing your current or past geographic location uploaded by you or others, or geographic indication information contained in photographs shared b you or others; (c) you can stop the collection of your geographic location information by closing positioning function. 2.4 In addition to the above information, OnePlus may also collect other non-personal information. Many kinds of these information are available and cannot be enumerated one by one. However, the information are automatically collected, stored, analyzed and used by machines, and not personally identifiable. III. HowMay OnePlus Use Information? 3.1 OnePlus may use the information collected in the course of providing services to you for the following purposes: 3.1.1 providing services to you; 3.1.2 carrying out identity authentication, customer service, safety precaution, fraud monitoring, archiving and backup at the time of providing services by OnePlus, so as to ensure the safety of the products and services provided by OnePlus to you; 3.1.3 assisting OnePlus in designing new services and improving existing services; 3.1.4 enabling OnePlus to better understand how you access and use OnePlus's services, so as to pertinently respond to your personalized needs, such as language setting, location setting, personalized help services and instructions, or respond to you or other users in other respects; 3.1.5 allowing you to participate in the investigation and research of OnePlus's products and services. 3.2 In order to allow you to have a better experience and improve OnePlus's services or other purposes you agree to, under the premise of complying with the relevant laws and regulations, OnePlus may use the information collected through a service for other services of OnePlus in a manner of bringing together information or in a personalized manner. If OnePlus provides appropriate options in the relevant service, you can also authorize OnePlus to use the information provided by and stored in the service for other services of OnePlus. IV. InformationOnePlus May Share 4.1 Without your consent, OnePlus and OnePlus's affiliates will not share your personal information with any third party, except for the following circumstances: 4.1.1 OnePlus and OnePlus's affiliates may share your personal information with OnePlus's affiliates, partners and third party service providers, contractors and agents (such as communication service providers sending e-mails or pushing notifications on behalf of OnePlus, and suppliers providing map services for location data to OnePlus) (they may not be in your jurisdiction) for the following purposes. If OnePlus or OnePlus's affiliates share your personal information with any of the above third parties, OnePlus will endeavor to ensure that when using your personal information, such third party will comply with this Privacy Policy and other proper confidentiality and safety measures that OnePlus requires such third party to comply with. (a) providing OnePlus's services to you; (b) achieving the purposes described in - How May OnePlus Use Information?; (c) performing OnePlus's obligations and exercising OnePlus’s rights under the End User License Agreement or this Privacy Policy; (d) understanding, maintaining and improving OnePlus's services. 4.1.2 OnePlus or OnePlus's affiliates may also retain, keep or disclose your personal information for the following needs: (a) complying with applicable laws and regulations; (b) complying with court orders or other legal procedures; (c) complying with the requirements of relevant governmental authorities; (d) achieving reasonable and necessary purposes for complying with applicable laws and regulations, safeguarding the public interests, or protecting the personal and property security or legitimate rights and interests of OnePlus's customers, OnePlus or OnePlus's group company, other users or employees. V. How Do You Access and Control Your Personal Information? 5.1 OnePlus will do everything possible to take appropriate technical means to ensure that you can access, update, correct, and delete your own registration information or other personal information provided by you when using OnePlus's services. When your access, update, correct, and delete the foregoing information, OnePlus may require you to authenticate your identity to protect the safety of your account. VI. InformationSafety 6.1 OnePlus retains your personal information only within the time required for the purposes stated in this Privacy Policy and within the time limit as required by laws and regulations. 6.2 OnePlus uses various management policies (such as, formulating information security system, signing confidentiality agreements with staff managing information, only allowing employees to access the collected information with a need of relevant work etc.), security technologies and procedures (such as, access with a need to enter a password, access control isolation, computer use monitoring, etc.) to prevent the loss of information, improper use, unauthorized access or disclosure. For example, in some services, OnePlus will use encryption technologies (such as SSL) to protect the personal information provided by you. But please understand that, due to technical constraints and the possible existence of a variety of malicious means, in the Internet industry, even if we do our best to strengthen security measures, it is impossible to always ensure that information is 100 percent safe. You need to know that something may go wrong with the system and communications network that your use to access to OnePlus's services due to factors beyond the control of OnePlus. 6.3 If the OnePlus is aware that the security of the data acquired and stored by it is endangered or that the non-public information of users is disclosed to an unrelated third party due to external actions (including but not limited to external security attacks), notwithstanding other disclaimers in this policy, OnePlus will take reasonable measures that it deems appropriate (including but not limited to internal investigation, reporting and notifying law enforcement agencies, cooperating with law enforcement agencies in work, etc.). At the same time, OnePlus will, in such circumstances as it thinks appropriate, take legal and reasonable measures to inform the relevant users of the information disclosed and the extent to which OnePlus is aware of such circumstance. VII. E-mails and Information OnePlus May Send to You 7.1 E-mails and Information Push When you use OnePlus's services, OnePlus may send e-mails, news, or push notifications to your device based on your uploaded communication modes or other means, and you agree to receive such information. 7.2 Service-Related Announcement OnePlus may issue a service-related announcement to you if necessary (for example, when a service is suspended due to system maintenance). You may not be able to cancel these announcements that are related to services and do not belong to popularization. VIII. ApplicationScope of Privacy Policy 8.1 This Privacy Policy shall be applied to all OnePlus's services, except that specific privacy policies are stipulated for certain specific services. For specific privacy policies for certain services, they will more specifically explain how OnePlus uses your information in such services. Such privacy policies for certain services shall constitute an integral part of this Privacy Policy. In case of any discrepancy between the privacy policies for certain services and this Privacy Policy, the privacy policies for certain services shall prevail. 8.2 Unless otherwise stipulated by this Privacy Policy, the terms used in this Privacy Policy shall have the same meanings as those defined in the End User License Agreement. 8.3 This Privacy Policy is written both in Chinese and English, the Chinese version shall prevail when there is any discrepancy between the two versions. IX. Exception to Application Scope of Privacy Policy 9.1 Please note that this Privacy Policy does not apply to the following information: 9.1.1 information collected by third party services (including any third party website) accessed through OnePlus's services; 9.1.2 information collected by other companies or agencies that provide advertising services in the OnePlus's service. 9.2 When using the above third party's social media services or other services (including any personal information you provide to such third party), you shall be subject to the service terms and privacy policy of the said third party (instead of this Privacy Policy), and need to read these terms carefully. 9.3 This Privacy Policy applies only to the information collected by OnePlus and does not apply to the services provided by any third party or third party information use rules. OnePlus does not assume any liability for any third party's use of the information provided by you. X. Juveniles' Use of Services of OnePlus 10.1 OnePlus demands that juveniles shall use OnePlus's products or services under the authority and guidance of their legal guardians 10.2 If you are a juvenile, you need to ensure that you have obtained consents of your legal guardians before providing personal information. XI. Amendment 11.1 OnePlus may amend the terms of this Privacy Policy at the right time, and such amendments shall constitute an integral part of this Privacy Policy. If the above amendments result in a substantial reduction in your rights under this Privacy Policy, OnePlus will notify you through agreed communication modes before the said amendment takes effect. In such case, if you continue to use the OnePlus's Services, this means that you agree to be bound by the amended Privacy Policy. XII. Information Feedback 12.1 If OnePlus needs to send any information to you, OnePlus will send the information to your e-mail address, mobile phone number, mailing address left by you at the time when you register your account or purchase products, or push the information directly through this software. Information sent by electronic communication mode shall be deemed effectively given at the time when your device or your used electronic system receives the information; and information sent by courier shall be deemed effectively given on the third day after they are sent by courier service. 12.2 If you have any comments, suggestions or questions about this Privacy Policy or OnePlus's products, please feel free to give OnePlus feedback at any time.
